<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/9278255-michelle"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1576617281i/9278255._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/9278255-michelle">Michelle</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Barbara,<br/>You might want to read the e-book novella &quot;Larger than Life&quot;. This tells the story of Alice in her childhood and college years and her decisio<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Barbara,<br />You might want to read the e-book novella "Larger than Life". This tells the story of Alice in her childhood and college years and her decision to go to Africa to study elephants. You get a clearer picture of Alice's mother's (Jenna's grandmother) personality and the conflicts between the two of them. Jenna's grandmother is not portrayed as a very warm person. There is also a 2nd novella "Where There's Smoke", and it tells Serenity's story about the senator's missing son that was the ruin of her career. One of them (can't remember which) is free on Amazon, and the other is only a few dollars. Hope you enjoy them.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
