    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2306029160" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2306029160" />
    <a title="Katie.dorny" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29183570-katie-dorny"><img alt="Katie.dorny" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519764068p2/29183570.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2306029160?book_show_action=true">Feb 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Katie.dorny" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Katie.dorny" href="/user/show/29183570-katie-dorny">Katie.dorny</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29183570-katie-dorny?shelf=2018">2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2306029160" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4754661303027748320">I adore this book. I&apos;ve read it twice now and when a few months have passed I never remember all the details and I get to be surprised again. <br/><br/>One of the perks of a rubbish memory! <br/><br/>It&apos;s a heart wrenching story with witty dialogue and I read it in one night as I couldn&apos;t bear to tear myself away from the story. Im excited to read her other novels now!</span>
  <span id="freeText4754661303027748320" style="display:none">I adore this book. I've read it twice now and when a few months have passed I never remember all the details and I get to be surprised again. <br /><br />One of the perks of a rubbish memory! <br /><br />It's a heart wrenching story with witty dialogue and I read it in one night as I couldn't bear to tear myself away from the story. Im excited to read her other novels now!</span>
