        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1081863195" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10649075897687971385">Ordinary life and the spirit world overlap and collide, as does who and what is real versus mystical or imagined. Even for someone who is not usually a fan of ghost stories and mysticism, the writing and storytelling compelled the suspension of disbelief and acceptance of the unimaginable. And in the end an amazed and admiring gasp—“I did not see that coming.”<br/><br/>There are so many strengths in the writing and story telling in Leaving Time. Check out my full review at New York Journal of Books<br/><br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/book-review/leaving-time'>http://</a></span>
  <span id="freeText10649075897687971385" style="display:none">Ordinary life and the spirit world overlap and collide, as does who and what is real versus mystical or imagined. Even for someone who is not usually a fan of ghost stories and mysticism, the writing and storytelling compelled the suspension of disbelief and acceptance of the unimaginable. And in the end an amazed and admiring gasp—“I did not see that coming.”<br /><br />There are so many strengths in the writing and story telling in Leaving Time. Check out my full review at New York Journal of Books<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/book-review/leaving-time">http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/book-...</a><br /><br /></span>
